    <item>
      <title>commitment and promise</title>
      <link>https://chang-wen-chen.github.io/2024/02/01/diff_commitment_promise/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 01 Feb 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://chang-wen-chen.github.io/2024/02/01/diff_commitment_promise/</guid>
      <description>TLDR&#xA;A commitment holds more weight than a simple promise They do differ in how they frame the distinction:&#xA;Emphasis on intent:&#xA;Commitment signifies a genuine desire to fulfill the promise, suggesting sincerity and motivation. Focus on strength:&#xA;Commitment implies a stronger promise than one can readily deliver highlighting its ambitious nature. Contrast with indulgence:&#xA;Commitment stands against indulgence, emphasizing dedication and perseverance as key differentiators. In essence, commitments go beyond empty promises, demonstrating a willingness to put in the effort and potentially exceed expectations.</description>
